Until now, telecommuting has been slower to take hold than many predicted when remote work technology first emerged.
(2019) found that jobseekers in China were more likely to apply for, and willing to accept lower pay, for positions that offered remote work.
For employees, working from home can reduce work-family conflict, especially for women.
A few high-profile companies, such as Yahoo and Reddit, have publicly moved away from remote work.
Many of the downsides of remote work apply to extensive rather than occasional telecommuting.